---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contrast - Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for Contrast - Sauna + Cold Plunge iOS app."
  ogUrl="https://idlefusion.com/contrast/privacy"
>
  <main>
    <section class="section-padding">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-12">Contrast - Sauna + Cold Plunge &middot; Effective February 11, 2026</p>

        <div class="space-y-8 text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">The Short Version</h2>
            <p>Contrast does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. Everything stays on your device.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Data Storage</h2>
            <p>All session data, settings, and personal records are stored locally on your device using SwiftData. No data is sent to any server, cloud service, or third party. There are no user accounts and no sign-up required.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Apple HealthKit</h2>
            <p class="mb-3">Contrast can save completed sessions to Apple Health as workouts, but only if you explicitly grant permission. HealthKit data is governed by <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[var(--accent-primary)] hover:underline">Apple's privacy policy</a> and never leaves your device through Contrast. If you deny HealthKit access, the app continues to work normally.</p>
            <p>Contrast does not read any health data from HealthKit. It only writes workout records for sessions you complete.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Analytics & Tracking</h2>
            <p>Contrast contains no analytics frameworks, no ad SDKs, no tracking pixels, and no telemetry of any kind. We do not use any third-party services that collect data.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Network Usage</h2>
            <p>Contrast makes no network requests. The app works entirely offline. The only network activity associated with the app is through the App Store for updates.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>Contrast does not knowingly collect any information from anyone, including children under the age of 13.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-3">Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>If this policy changes, we will update this page with the new effective date. Since Contrast collects no data, meaningful changes are unlikely.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
